      "type": "ValidationResult",
      "name": "Bench-scale hemolysis index comparison — FDA generic pump",
      "description": "Computational hemolysis index (HI) predictions compared against in-vitro measurements from the FDA benchmark dataset for the generic centrifugal pump. Predictions within 18% of measured HI across four of five operating points; fifth point (high-speed, low-flow) exceeds tolerance band. Validation performed against the pre-revision model build using the 2025-Q4 rheological dataset."
    },
    {
      "id": "https://uofa.net/synth/validation/morrison-cou2-monte-carlo-uq",
      "type": "ValidationResult",
      "name": "Monte Carlo uncertainty quantification on hemolysis predictions",
      "description": "500-sample Monte Carlo propagation of input uncertainties (viscosity, yield stress, damage exponent) through the CFD hemolysis model. 95th-percentile HI remains below clinical threshold at 3 of 5 operating conditions. Input distributions derived from the 2025-Q4 rheological dataset; re-sampling against the revised model has not been completed."
    }
  ],
