    "role": "Credibility assessment team",
    "outcome": "Accepted",
    "rationale": "The credibility assessment team determined that the seven assessed factors, while each falling one gradation below the required level for MRL 5, collectively provide sufficient confidence for a Low assurance level submission. The six unassessed factors are acknowledged as epistemic gaps; remediation plans are in place for Q2 2026, including re-validation of model inputs against the revised model build using updated rheological data. The team accepted the package on the basis that the planned re-validation activities will be completed prior to regulatory submission and that no safety-critical decisions will be made on the basis of this package alone.",
